The paper focuses on developing a robust, real-time LOAM algorithm for LiDARs with small FoV and irregular samplings, which is a common problem in robotics and autonomous vehicles. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also involves computer vision techniques for mapping and localization, which suggests cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the second likely sub-category. The authors also mention machine learning and optimization techniques, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper addresses the challenges of autonomous navigation and safe path planning, which could be relevant to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
